lace sub-pack boundaries inside side-branch ancestry ([#41](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/41))\n- `--progress` for live per-side throughput across `sync`, `replicate`, `bootstrap`, and `fetch`, with rolling-window rate, hostname-aware labels, inline pack subdivision, and an end-of-run summary under `--stats` ([#37](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/37))\n- Per-subcommand `--help` after the CLI moved to cobra; bare `git-sync` lists subcommands on stdout instead of printing the full usage block as an error ([#35](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/35))\n- README cover image and embedded demo videos for `git-sync plan` and `git-sync sync` ([#30](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/30), [#31](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/31))","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"2fa26108-62b4-41d7-adde-51078b10e541","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync","sessionId":"aefcb05b-206d-434a-94bf-d11991a74a0a","version":"2.1.129","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"4016b92a-93d0-480f-852f-1d7d692942b7","isSidechain":false,"attachment":{"type":"edited_text_file","filename":"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/CHANGELOG.md","snippet":"1\t# Changelog\n2\t\n3\tAll notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.\n4\t\n5\tThe format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/),\n6\tand this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/).\n7\t\n8\t## [0.4.3] - 2026-05-07\n9\t\n10\t### Added\n11\t\n12\t- `--bootstrap-strategy=topo` for merge-heavy repos: walks every reachable commit in deterministic topological order so batched bootstrap can place sub-pack boundaries inside side-branch ancestry ([#41](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/41))\n13\t- `--progress` for live per-side throughput across `sync`, `replicate`, `bootstrap`, and `fetch`, with rolling-window rate, hostname-aware labels, inline pack subdivision, and an end-of-run summary under `--stats` ([#37](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/37))\n14\t- Per-subcommand `--help` after the CLI moved to cobra; bare `git-sync` lists subcommands on stdout instead of printing the full usage block as an error ([#35](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/35))\n15\t- README cover image and embedded demo videos for `git-sync plan` and `git-sync sync` ([#30](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/30), [#31](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/31))\n16\t\n17\t### Changed\n18\t\n19\t- Batched bootstrap stream-parses the pack and aborts doomed pushes ~5% in instead of waiting for the body-limit rejection; subdivision converges in 1–2 rounds instead of 6+ on blob-heavy repos ([#40](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/40))\n20\t- Post-rejection subdivision sizes splits from observed pack bytes (4× when the server cut us off mid-stream, 2× otherwise) and ratchets the bytes-per-object estimate up after each 413 ([#38](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/38))\n21\t- Batched bootstrap recombines upcoming checkpoints when consecutive packs underuse the target limit, recovering pack granularity after heavy regions; already-pushed checkpoints are also passed as fetch `have`s on later rounds ([#42](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/42))\n22\t- Relay-only syncs skip the upfront `FetchToStore`; the materialized fallback lazy-fetches the source closure only when force, prune, or divergent refs require it ([#34](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/34))\n23\t\n24\t### Fixed\n25\t\n26\t- Sync into targets that share reachability with the source: tolerate pruned objects in the materialized walker, accept branch creates and `no-thin` targets in incremental relay, and surface diagnostic headers (`Cf-Ray`, `Server`, `X-Request-Id`) on opaque 5xx ([#33](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/33))\n27\t\n28\t## [0.4.2] - 2026-04-30\n29\t\n30\tFirst public release. `git-sync` mirrors refs from a source remote to a target\n31\tremote without a local checkout, streaming source packs directly into target\n32\t`receive-pack` whenever possible. The release covers the CLI, the library API,\n33\tand the protocol plumbing they share.\n34\t\n35\t### Added\n36\t\n37\t- `git-sync sync` — relay-based mirror that streams source `upload-pack`\n38\t  output into target `receive-pack` without materializing the object graph\n39\t  locally. Falls back to an in-memory `go-git` store, bounded by\n40\t  `--materialized-max-objects`, when relay is not eligible (force, prune,\n41\t  deletes, tag retargets) ([#1](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/1),\n42\t  [#2](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/2)).\n43\t- `git-sync replicate` and `git-sync plan --mode replicate` for\n44\t  source-authoritative, relay-only replication. Divergent branches and tags\n45\t  are retargeted against the source; `--prune` deletes orphan managed refs.\n46\t  Relay-only by design: no materialized fallback\n47\t  ([#4](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/4)).\n48\t- `git-sync plan` — preview the actions a `sync` or `replicate` would take,\n49\t  with structured JSON output suitable for automation.\n50\t- `git-sync bootstrap` — initial-seed path for empty targets, with adaptive\n51\t  batching, trunk-first planning to cut per-branch graph fetches, and\n52\t  resume-from-stale-temp-refs recovery\n53\t  ([#6](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/6)).\n54\t- `git-sync version` subcommand with build metadata\n55\t  ([#26](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/26)).\n56\t- Reusable Go library at `entire.io/entire/git-sync`. The stable surface\n57\t  (`Probe`, `Plan`, `Sync`, `Replicate`, typed results, auth and HTTP\n58\t  injection) lives at the module root; advanced controls (`Bootstrap`,\n59\t  `Fetch`, batching knobs, heap measurement) live in\n60\t  `entire.io/entire/git-sync/unstable`\n61\t  ([#3](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/3),\n62\t  [#17](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/17)).\n63\t- Git protocol v2 source-side support: `ls-refs`, `fetch` with v2\n64\t  acknowledgments and response-end handling, capability negotiation, and\n65\t  graceful fallback when the source does not advertise v2.\n66\t- Smart HTTP transport: pkt-line primitives, sideband demultiplexing, info/refs\n67\t  advertisement validation, smart endpoint path normalization, oversized\n68\t  packet rejection, empty pkt-line acceptance, and v2 fetch remote `ERR`\n69\t  packet handling.\n70\t- Optional info/refs redirect following on the source endpoint, exposed\n71\t  through the public `gitsync` API\n72\t  ([#9](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/9)).\n73\t- Git credential helper fallback and `--source-token` / `--target-token`\n74\t  flags for HTTPS auth.\n75\t- JSON output mode with a stable schema and camelCase keys across all\n76\t  commands ([#7](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/7)).\n77\t- Adaptive bootstrap batching: auto-subdivide on target body-size rejection,\n78\t  pre-check PACK header object count before pushing oversized batches, and\n79\t  shared `--max-pack-bytes` / `--target-max-pack-bytes` flags across `sync`,\n80\t  `replicate`, `plan`, and `bootstrap`.\n81\t- Sideband progress streamed to stderr when `-v` is set.\n82\t- Homebrew tap install via `brew tap entireio/tap && brew install --cask git-sync`\n83\t  ([#25](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/25)).\n84\t- GoReleaser-based release pipeline for cross-platform binaries\n85\t  ([#26](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/26)).\n86\t- Identical source and target endpoints are rejected before any network\n87\t  round-trips.\n88\t- Documentation set: `docs/usage.md`, `docs/architecture.md`,\n89\t  `docs/protocol.md`, `docs/testing.md`, plus README installation,\n90\t  quick-start, and FAQ ([#21](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/21),\n91\t  [#22](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/22),\n92\t  [#23](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/23))."},"type":"attachment","uuid":"9a45306e-dadc-4ce5-8353-8458c3630979","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:46:36.487Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync","sessionId":"aefcb05b-206d-434a-94bf-d11991a74a0a","version":"2.1.129","gitBranch":"main"}
