{"parentUuid":"15312052-254c-4907-8256-9102f0bc051d","isSidechain":false,"type":"system","subtype":"away_summary","content":"Working on issue #47 to clarify git-sync's force semantics: branch `soph/force-clarification` has three commits splitting `--force` into `--force-with-lease` and `--force-blind` with a lease-failure error hint. Next: open the PR with the description I drafted.","timestamp":"2026-05-13T13:26:18.902Z","uuid":"a40e2310-7847-4efa-b133-3fcf15f6beef","isMeta":false,"userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync","sessionId":"aefcb05b-206d-434a-94bf-d11991a74a0a","version":"2.1.129","gitBranch":"soph/force-clarification"}
{"parentUuid":"a40e2310-7847-4efa-b133-3fcf15f6beef","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"d97ab733-e2d6-41ac-8b6e-be2e2ff52299","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Findings:\n\n1. High: `BestEffort` currently defeats the new `--force-with-lease` guarantee. In [internal/syncer/syncer.go](/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/internal/syncer/syncer.go:634), any best-effort run installs `OnRejection` for all per-ref `ng` statuses. Then [internal/gitproto/push.go](/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/internal/gitproto/push.go:172) skips `report.Error()` entirely when that callback is present, so lease-mismatch statuses get downgraded to warnings instead of failing the run. That means `sync --all-refs --force-with-lease` can exit successfully after a concurrent target update, which contradicts the documented lease semantics.\n\n2. Medium: the public and unstable APIs no longer reject invalid force combinations at the request edge. [client.go](/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/client.go:146) validates URLs/protocol/mappings, but never rejects `ForceWithLease && ForceBlind` or `ModeReplicate` plus force flags. The unstable client has the same issue: [unstable/client.go](/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/unstable/client.go:152) goes straight into `buildSyncConfig`, and the actual rejection only happens later in [internal/syncer/syncer.go](/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/internal/syncer/syncer.go:569). That’s a regression from the stated “fail before I/O / at the API edge” intent, and it also means custom auth providers may run before the request is rejected.\n\n3. Low: the updated docs now describe `replicate` incorrectly. [docs/usage.md](/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/docs/usage.md:248) says “replicate is fast-forward-only by design,” but the implementation and tests still treat it as overwrite-oriented replication; for example [internal/syncer/integration_test.go](/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/internal/syncer/integration_test.go:2576) explicitly asserts divergent tag overwrite succeeds in replicate mode. That wording will mislead users choosing between `sync` and `replicate`.\n\nI also tried to run `go test ./internal/gitproto ./internal/syncer ./cmd/git-sync`, but the sandbox blocks `httptest` from binding a local port, so I couldn’t use test execution to validate these paths here."},"uuid":"f97d2852-9272-41a3-85e8-9f13f1dc931f","timestamp":"2026-05-13T14:19:33.998Z","permissionMode":"acceptEdits","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync","sessionId":"aefcb05b-206d-434a-94bf-d11991a74a0a","version":"2.1.129","gitBranch":"soph/force-clarification"}
