{"parentUuid":"c2e50a50-84cd-4341-88eb-2e8ebf5ef081","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"70c41555-112c-4dd8-a78f-f13f7aa899c2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"One remaining finding:\n\n1. Medium: lease-failure escalation is now applied unconditionally to every best-effort rejection, even when the run did not use `--force-with-lease`. [internal/syncer/syncer.go](/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/internal/syncer/syncer.go:433) treats any `gitproto.IsLeaseFailure(status)` rejection as fatal, and both sync and replicate call it unconditionally after `finalizeCounts` at [internal/syncer/syncer.go](/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/internal/syncer/syncer.go:825) and [internal/syncer/syncer.go](/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/internal/syncer/syncer.go:922). But `IsLeaseFailure` currently matches broad strings like `\"non-fast-forward\"` and `\"fetch first\"` in [internal/gitproto/push.go](/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/internal/gitproto/push.go:112). That is correct for `--force-with-lease`, but wrong for `--force-blind` or non-force best-effort runs: those same server messages can reflect ordinary policy rejection rather than a stale lease. As written, `sync --all-refs --force-blind` can fail fatally on a rejection that the docs describe as warnable best-effort behavior, even though no lease semantics are in effect. This check should be gated on `s.cfg.ForceWithLease` or otherwise distinguish true lease-mode pushes from all other rejection paths.\n\nThe earlier issues I flagged were fixed: request-edge policy validation is back, and the replicate docs now match the implementation. I couldn’t re-run the full Go test suite here because the sandbox still blocks `httptest` from binding local ports."},"uuid":"b31997ac-b924-4cfe-9695-648773743156","timestamp":"2026-05-13T14:27:47.589Z","permissionMode":"acceptEdits","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync","sessionId":"aefcb05b-206d-434a-